WHAT WE FOUND
===========================================================================

  HIGHEST-PRECISION DOWNSTREAM DATA:
  1. Optical clock frequency ratios: 15-18 digits
     PSLQ: ALL NULL at maxcoeff 1000

  2. Hydrogen/deuterium isotopologue ratios: 8-10 digits
     PSLQ: ALL NULL at maxcoeff 1000

  3. Molecular transition frequencies: 11-15 digits
     Not dimensionless — need ratios

  4. BCS gap ratios: 3-4 digits (too imprecise)

  The optical clock ratios are THE most precisely measured
  dimensionless numbers in existence (~10^-17). They depend
  on α, m_e/m_p, and nuclear structure through atomic physics.
  They are downstream. They are precise. And they are NULL
  against the transcendental basis.

  YOUR INSTINCT WAS RIGHT: there IS high-precision downstream
  data we hadn't tested. But the result is the same: null.
  The transcendental basis doesn't connect to these ratios
  any more than it connects to the SM free parameters directly.
  